<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Legitimate" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Legitimate,</orth> 1) lawfully begotten: <bibl n="shak. jn 1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.179" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 16</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 16</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 16</bibl><lb />2) logically deduced, logical: <cit><quote>I will prove it l., sir, upon the oaths of judgment and reason,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 15</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Illegitimate</emph>).</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>